A lady suspected to be infected with the novel Corona Virus, who allegedly escaped from an isolation centre in Abuja, has been intercepted in Akwanga, Nasarawa State. She was tracked by security personnel through her phone number to Kurmin Tagwaye, a suburb of Akwanga, in Nasarawa. The lady, who hails from Ibadan, allegedly escaped from an isolation centre in Abuja and headed to Akwanga. A source who saw the lady said “I received a call from security personnel in Abuja, that they tracked the contact of a lady who escaped isolation from Abuja, to Akwanga. “Immediately I got the call, I swung into action by calling my people in Kurmin Tagwaye village in Akwanga, and they traced the lady in a house,” he said. The lady was traced to the house of one Deacon Moses, behind ERCC Church, Kurmin Tagwaye along Wamba road in Akwanga and taken to the isolation centre at General Hospital, Akwanga. It was gathered that the family of Deacon Moses, have gone on self-isolation pending the outcome of the result of the lady. In the meantime, another victim from Rinze, in Akwanga, who returned from Kano, recently with the suspected case of coronavirus have also been isolated at the General Hospital Akwanga. A source at the Akwanga General Hospital, said the lady was brought in Saturday morning, while the other suspect from Rinze, was brought in on Thursday. Nasarawa State Commissioner for Health, pharmacist Mohammed Ahmed Yahaya said, “We have isolated some people, they are all isolated as suspected patients of Coronavirus pending the outcome of the results.” Nasarawa State is yet to record an index case of Coronavirus or COVID-19.